declare_parcel_as_script_with_stdin <<'/---'
Handle *process* (i.e., currently running commands) aliases.
/---

# ....................{ SETTERS                            }....................
declare_alias_with_stdin\
    'void set_integer_to_pid_command_prior(string integer_name)'\
    '{ set_integer_to_integer "$(get_stdin)" "${!}" } <<<' <<'/---'
Set the passed integer to the process identifier (PID) of the most recent
command executed in the background. This includes commands appended by `&`,
commands prefixed by `bg`, and the coprocess of the current shell.
/---

# --------------------( WASTELANDS                         )--------------------
